Open corridor D3.

146
00:10:46,945 --> 00:10:47,125
Fine!

147
00:10:51,562 --> 00:10:52,482
I'll do it here then.

148
00:10:53,223 --> 00:10:55,765
Open corridor...

149
00:10:55,785 --> 00:10:55,805
D3.

150
00:10:55,825 --> 00:10:59,488
You will be eating all the spells I make.

151
00:10:59,688 --> 00:11:03,371
I'm already inclined to obey your orders, but certainly your machines.

152
00:11:03,912 --> 00:11:05,874
Come on, ass, stop getting sassy with me!

153
00:11:06,354 --> 00:11:10,037
Stop... getting... sassy with me.

154
00:11:10,297 --> 00:11:12,699
You seem to really like to play with that.

155
00:11:12,819 --> 00:11:14,781
I'm sure you'll be able to handle it.

156
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:16,743
Oh, what happened?

157
00:11:18,459 --> 00:11:22,683
Woah, what did I do? I'm sorry! Oh god, you are a fucked up AI, aren't you?

158
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:23,384
Ooh!

159
00:11:27,108 --> 00:11:32,794
Okay, so this is a very usual reaction and behavior from a player playing Even Zero.

160
00:11:33,714 --> 00:11:40,341
I think 80% of the players of Even Zero start the game like this, giving orders, like in a text-adventure game.

161
00:11:42,364 --> 00:11:50,533
Our goal as chatbot makers is to change their mind and make them think with the emotional part of the brain.

162
00:11:50,653 --> 00:11:55,359
And it starts by making them treat the chatbot as a sensible being.

163
00:11:56,020 --> 00:12:00,645
So what we see in this video is Jacksepticeye keeps asking the same order.

164
00:12:00,885 --> 00:12:02,087
Open the door, open the door.

165
00:12:03,235 --> 00:12:13,023
And the AI is able to count that and is able to realize that the player isn't yet treating it as a sensible being.

166
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:16,548
This scene has just one purpose.

167
00:12:16,808 --> 00:12:20,951
The door won't open as long as the player will give just simple orders.

168
00:12:21,511 --> 00:12:26,914
If the player asks, please, it's a polite word and it's the first step, so the door will open.

169
00:12:27,414 --> 00:12:32,437
If the player insults the area, it's also the first step, because starting the moment you insult someone,

170
00:12:32,757 --> 00:12:35,739
it means that you consider it has feelings, you're just mean.

171
00:12:36,299 --> 00:12:37,219
But it's still fine.

172
00:12:39,534 --> 00:12:42,275
What we see here is that after several orders,

173
00:12:42,755 --> 00:12:45,116
the AI gives a cue and says,

174
